{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is the handoff between source clients, aggregation/orchestration, and the summary input builder. A unit test of only the merge function can miss wiring mistakes (e.g., one client result never forwarded).","test_description":"Run the report assembly path with three source adapters returning distinct sentinel payloads, then assert the payload sent into summary generation contains all three sections with correct source attribution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior depends on cross-module error handling: source failure, fallback section rendering, and continuation of report generation. Single-function tests do not validate that pipeline continuity is preserved.","test_description":"Execute the collection-and-render flow with one source adapter raising a realistic fetch exception while the other two succeed; verify report generation completes and the failed section contains `data unavailable` instead of terminating the run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness here is about model output quality/faithfulness to inputs, which is a real LLM behavior concern and can vary across runs/prompts. Mocking or stubbing summary output would hide the exact failure mode.","test_description":"Feed fixed input datasets with known key values to the real summary-generation model and evaluate whether generated narratives preserve those values (with tolerance criteria for wording but strict checks on factual numbers/statuses). Run repeatedly to detect drift/non-deterministic misstatements.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This crosses real external boundaries (HTTP/internal APIs + email transport + inbox delivery). Mocked transport can pass while real auth, formatting, SMTP/API, or deliverability issues fail.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end execution against reachable test instances of data sources and real email delivery path to a test inbox; assert the message is received by configured recipients with expected subject/body and attached/generated report content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure boundary includes real delivery-service unreachability plus persistence/retry across runs. Mocking email can hide real timeout/connection exception behavior and retry trigger conditions.","test_description":"Perform two real runs: first with email endpoint intentionally unreachable to force fallback, then verify report is persisted to local retry storage; second run with service restored, verify queued report is retried and delivered, and retry artifact is cleared/marked sent.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.35,"System":0.55,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.05}}]}
